a-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 09, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104pcn1665702834745.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/pcn1665702834745.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/pcn1665702834745.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"pcn1665702834745\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Is Independent Form </h1>\n<div class=\"body refbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Form property that determines whether the form can be moved independently of other\n      forms, or whether it overlays another form. </p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"pcn1665702834745__section_w5141ab1b5b1_w5142ab1b5_w5143ab1\">\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"pcn1665702834745__table_d11756e1_d11757e1_d11758e1\"><caption></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"pcn1665702834745__table_d11756e1_d11757e1_d11758e1__entry__1\"> Value </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"pcn1665702834745__table_d11756e1_d11757e1_d11758e1__entry__2\"> Description </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"pcn1665702834745__table_d11756e1_d11757e1_d11758e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">True</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"pcn1665702834745__table_d11756e1_d11757e1_d11758e1__entry__2\"> The form does not overlay the previous form\n                        and can be moved. </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"pcn1665702834745__table_d11756e1_d11757e1_d11758e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">False</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"pcn1665702834745__table_d11756e1_d11757e1_d11758e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">The form is displayed on top of the previous form and cannot be moved. If\n                           the current form is intended to overlay another, specify the form\n                           instance that it will overlay in the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Parent Form</span>\n                           field.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"pcn1665702834745__section_l1l_bkm_twb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d593625e115\">Description</h2>\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"pcn1665702834745__note_hgc_jkm_twb\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> For contained forms (which have the\n               <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Window Type</span> property set to <code class=\"ph codeph\">Contained</code>), the\n            value of this property is ignored and always treated as <code class=\"ph codeph\">false</code> .</div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"pcn1665702834745__p_d100469e1_d100470e1_d100471e1\">When <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Is Independent Form</span> is\n               <code class=\"ph codeph\">False</code>, be aware of the following:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"pcn1665702834745__ul_ngc_jkm_twb\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"pcn1665702834745__li_d40529e1_d40530e1_d40531e1\">The <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Is Independent Form</span>\n               property cannot be used in combination with the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Caption</span>,\n                  <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Resizable</span>, or <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">System Menu</span>\n               properties. </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"pcn1665702834745__li_d40532e1_d40533e1_d40534e1\">Panels are not shown on an independent form. If\n               the underlying form has a panel, the panel will be used by the form that overlays it.\n               However, for user-defined buttons to work in the overlay form, the operations also\n               need to be defined in the overlay form. </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"pcn1665702834745__li_d40535e1_d40536e1_d40537e1\">If the underlying form contains one or more split\n               bars, the overlay form is attached to a split bar and window borders. This can affect\n               the size and position of the overlay form. </li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"pcn1665702834745__section_rh1_nkm_twb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d593625e166\">Applies To</h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"pcn1665702834745__ul_egt_nkm_twb\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"pcn1665702834745__li_d40451e1_d40452e1_d40453e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"euw1665702582150.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/euw1665702582150.html\" title=\"A Form is a stateful presentation Component that enables users to view and modify data in a Windows or character mode application.\">Form</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/lsu1665702783988.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Parent Form (TABPAGE)</a><p>Name of form instance that the current form will overlay. This ensures that the current form is only displayed over the specified parent, and disappears when focus is switches to another form instance. This property can only be set if the current form is a Contained Form or if the property Is Independent Form is false.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ecw1665702715443.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>System Menu (SysMenu)</a><p>Window property of a form or application shell that determines whether the Windows system menu and buttons to minimize, maximize, and close the window are available for this window. Valid values: True or False.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/kjr1676877187333.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Resizable (CanResize)</a><p>Window property of a form or application shell that determines whether the window can be resized at runtime.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/kno1665702715076.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Caption</a><p>Window property that determines whether the form window has a title bar. Valid values: True (default) or False.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3615160\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3615160\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Is Independent Form Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 09, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Is Independent Form Form property that determines whether the form can be moved independently of other forms, or whether it overlays another form. Value Description True The form does not overlay the previous form and can be moved. False The form is displayed on top of the previous form and cannot be moved. If the current form is intended to overlay another, specify the form instance that it will overlay in the Parent Form field. Description Note: For contained forms (which have the Window Type property set to Contained ), the value of this property is ignored and always treated as false . When Is Independent Form is False , be aware of the following: The Is Independent Form property cannot be used in combination with the Caption , Resizable , or System Menu properties. Panels are not shown on an independent form. If the underlying form has a panel, the panel will be used by the form that overlays it. However, for user-defined buttons to work in the overlay form, the operations also need to be defined in the overlay form. If the underlying form contains one or more split bars, the overlay form is attached to a split bar and window borders. This can affect the size and position of the overlay form. Applies To Form Related Links Parent Form (TABPAGE) Name of form instance that the current form will overlay. This ensures that the current form is only displayed over the specified parent, and disappears when focus is switches to another form instance. This property can only be set if the current form is a Contained Form or if the property Is Independent Form is false. System Menu (SysMenu) Window property of a form or application shell that determines whether the Windows system menu and buttons to minimize, maximize, and close the window are available for this window. Valid values: True or False. Resizable (CanResize) Window property of a form or application shell that determines whether the window can be resized at runtime. Caption Window property that determines whether the form window has a title bar. Valid values: True (default) or False. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}